    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Short, cape-shaped garments that coveri the shoulders and reach only to the elbow, with an open front, which may be fastened by means of a row of small buttons; at the neck it has a very small and purely ornamental hood. The privilege of wearing the mozzetta belongs properly to no one but the pope, cardinals, exempt abbots, abbots general, and the four prelates di fiochetti.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079245/Catholic Encyclopedia [online] (2003-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een door bisschoppen en domheren gedragen schoudermantel die ruim over de ellebogen hangt en aan de voorzijde is gesloten met knoopjes. De mozetta tekent de jurisdictie van de drager en wordt alleen in dat gebied gedragen waar deze rechtsmacht bezit. Zie ook: cappa magna</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
